                <h2>Off-Season Destinations: </h2>
                <p style="line-height:20px;">Everyone travels according to the season to get the best experience of their desired destination, obviously. But did you know airlines increase their flight ticket prices during peak seasons? Yes, many airlines take advantage of seasonal travel and charge you extra for your last minute flight tickets. But if you buy a last minute airline ticket to an off-season destination, it will surely cost you less. For example, tropical summer cities like Goa, Andaman & Nicobar, Chennai, etc. If you wish to travel last minute, then opt for an off-season destination and save big on your last minute flight tickets.</p>
                <h2>Best Time to Book:</h2>
                <p style="line-height:20px;">Travelers can book their last minute flight tickets no less than a week prior to their travel plan. Even if you book your flight 14 day before your desired travel date, it will be considered last minute. If you buy an airline ticket during this time, you can still save a lot on your flight ticket. You can avail amazing discounts on booking your last minute flight to one of our popular domestic routes.</p>
                <h2>Find Best Deals & Discounts: </h2>
                <p style="line-height:20px;">Did you know you get miles points every time you book a flight ticket? Yes, most airlines offer miles, and you can use those mile points to get discounted prices on your next flight tickets. Also, online travel agency websites, such as Flightsmojo.in, offer discounted flight tickets during festival seasons like Diwali, Christmas, Holi, etc. Make sure to research all the available options before you buy your last minute flight tickets.</p>
                <h2>Compare Airlines and Fare: </h2>
                <p style="line-height:20px;">Different airlines offer different prices on their flight tickets. These prices differ based on all the services they provide on the said flight tickets. Such as economy, premium economy, first class, and business class flights all come with different services. One offers more leg room; the other provides better seats and lounge services. You can compare the various airlines and their perks & benefits and make your decisions.</p>
